description.p:
1. some labels do not allow of deactivation, so that these labels have to be removed by hand;


2. after deactivation, some labels become active again because the short-circuit between the capacitor plates disappears spontaneously as a result of the handling and deformation of the label;


3. they are not reactivatable.

As for source-tagging, whereby a label is integrated into the product or into the package thereof, the above means that:


either the label coming from the factory must be in the non-active state and may only be activated in the shop where a shoplifting system is present;


or all shopkeepers should have a deactivation device available.

